countOrders().details: - Return number of all created orders.

create(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.details: - Create an order to be executed on OneInch before expiration. If `srcTokenAddr` is ETH, `srcAmount` has to be included in msg.value. If `srcTokenAddr` isn't ETH, make sure that msg.sender has approved  to spend `srcTokenAddr` in `srcAmount` amount. In both cases, one should provide additional ETH in msg.value that would serve as a reward for the one who calls `execute(orderId,calldata)`.

params.minReturnAmount: - min expected amount of target ERC20 (in minimal divisible units)
params.period: - period in seconds after which order cannot be executed
params.srcAmount: - amount of input ERC20 to be swapped (in minimal divisible units)

execute(uint256,bytes).details: - Execute order. On successful execution, msg.sender gets `execReward` provided by order's `beneficiary`.

params.oneInchCallData: - data obtained from "/swap" endpoint of 1inch API

update(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: - Update `minReturnAmount` and `expiration` of an existing order.

params.minReturnAmount: - min number of dstToken to be received
params.period: - period in seconds after which order cannot be executed
